John E. LUKENBILL v. Walter A. HUNTER, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 3595. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 8, 1948. Edward E. Pringle, of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Randolph Carpenter, U. S. Atty., and Eugene W. Davis, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, HUXMAN, and MURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment reversed and cause remanded for further proceedings without written opinion.
